UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 897
1 which are located on the:
2 (a) Interstate highway system; or
3 (b) State highway system for prices or fees below the prevailing market rate.
4 (4) A sponsorship agreement shall allow the installation of acknowledgment signs
5 within welcome centers and rest areas and on the portion of the interstate
6 highway system and state highway system and associated rights-of-way near
7 welcome centers and rest areas.
8 (5) The cabinet shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS
9 Chapter 13A to establish a sponsorship policy and process to enter into
10 sponsorship agreements to install acknowledgment signs at welcome centers and
11 rest areas.
12 (6) The sponsorship policy for sponsorship agreements that applies to all welcome
13 centers and rest areas shall:
14 (a) Be subject to approval by the Federal Highway Administration;
15 (b) Include requirements that eligible sponsors comply with state and federal
16 law prohibiting discrimination based on race, color, national origin, age,
17 sex, religion, disability, or any other federally protected class;
18 (c) Include language requiring the cabinet to terminate a sponsorship
19 agreement if it determines the sponsorship agreement or acknowledgment
20 sign:
21 1. Presents a safety concern;
22 2. Interferes with the free and safe flow of traffic; or
23 3. Is not in the public interest; and
24 (d) Describe the types of sponsors and sponsorship agreements that are
25 acceptable and consistent with applicable state and federal law.
26 (7) A person or private entity that enters into a sponsorship agreement with the
27 cabinet shall pay the costs of:
Page 2 of 3
XXXX 11/12/2025 12:42 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 897
1 (a) Manufacturing and installing an acknowledgment sign;
2 (b) Placing a sponsorship message on a sign or marker; and
3 (c) Removing all acknowledgment signs, messages, and markers after the
4 expiration or termination of the sponsorship agreement.
5 (8) An acknowledgment sign shall:
6 (a) Identify the sponsor as a sponsor of the welcome center or rest area and
7 include the name and logo of the sponsor;
8 (b) Not include, identify, or promote alcohol or tobacco products, adult-
9 oriented establishments, political candidacies, political issue advocacy, or
10 political campaign advertising;
11 (c) Not resemble an official traffic control device; and
12 (d) Comply with federal outdoor advertising regulations in accordance with 23
13 U.S.C. sec. 131.
